Coinvolti dalla slavina anche i due amici, di 26 e 36 anni, che sono riusciti a salvarsi e a dare l'allarme. I soccorritori hanno raggiunto il posto della tragedia a piedi, per un forte vento l'elicottero non ha potuto intervenire.

Stavano effettuando un'escursione vicino al lago di Morasco: a differenza dei suoi compagni non aveva il sistema di localizzazione Arva. E' stato recuperato già morto dopo quasi due ore dall'incidente.";s:4:"date";s:19:"2013-03-31 12:00:00";s:10:"categories";a:1:{i:0;s:15:"DANGER MODERATE";}s:5:"point";a:2:{i:0;d:46.43342899999999673354977858252823352813720703125;i:1;d:8.373188999999999992951416061259806156158447265625;}}i:16;a:7:{s:2:"id";i:273;s:5:"title";s:32:"Skier dies in Scottish avalanche";s:4:"link";s:49:"http://geoavalanche.org/incident/reports/view/273";s:11:"description";s:1524:"The body of an off piste skier missing since Saturday has been found near the Glencoe ski area. It follows days of heavy snowfall and high winds. A body was discovered around mid-day on Sunday. Next of kin have been informed. 

He has been named 41-year old  Daniel Maddox from Clackmannanshire. 

The accident happened on Saturday and despite a large search operation by the emergency services the body was not found unitl Easter Sunday.

The avalanche travelled 300m and ended up in a gully where the snow was up to 15 m deep. 

In some place the avalanche poles of the rescue services were not long enogh to reach the bottom of the slide.

His body was eventually found 7m under the snow.

"Our guys have been out digging deep trenches and probing from there, as our poles are obviously not long enough to do it from the surface of the snow. The missing man is an extremely experienced skier and we will continue looking until we find him," said the leader of the Glencoe Mountain Rescue Team, John Greive, as the search operation continued.

Glencoe Mountain Resort posted news of the accident on its Facebook page.

"Glencoe Mountain Resort regret to say that an experienced off piste skier skiing out with the ski area was caught in a major avalanche this afternoon. Mountain Rescue Teams and Glencoe Ski patrol have been on site for the last 4hrs."

Around 30 people were involved in the search.

